LY the function implementation (no imports needed, no prints, no tests, no main, no extra text).\\n- Ensure the directory exists and then write the file to disk. After writing, read it back to verify persistence. Report completion with the absolute path and a short confirmation.",\n            "send_to": "Alex"\n        }\n    },\n    {\n        "command_name": "RoleZero.reply_to_human",\n        "args": {\n            "content": "I have created a task and dispatched it to Alex (Engineer). He will implement add(lst) in Python to sum even elements at odd indices, save it as add.py at /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT-2/humaneval_baseline/add.py, ensure the file contains only the function, and verify it is written to disk. I will notify you as soon as he confirms completion."\n        }\n    },\n    {\n        "command_name": "end",\n        "args": {}\n    }\n]\n```'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': 'Command Plan.append_task executed\n\nCommand TeamLeader.publish_team_message executed\n\nCommand RoleZero.reply_to_human executed: SUCCESS, human has received your reply. Refrain from resending duplicate messages.  If you no longer need to take action, use the command ‘end’ to stop.\n\nCommand end executed:'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '[Message] from Mike to Alex: Team,\n\nTask: Implement and save a Python 3 function.\n\nHigh-level goal: create a small function that computes a sum based on elements from an input list; include negative numbers where relevant. The specific selection criteria (which indices or parity to include), function name, and exact signature were lost in transmission — make a reasonable design choice and add a brief comment at the top of the file explaining your assumptions.\n\nKeep the implementation minimal and self-contained (no tests or extra scripts). Commit the file to the repository and reply with the file path and a short confirmation when complete.'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '[Message] from Alex(Engineer) to Mike: I have finished the 